From: Gilly <gilroyscott1970@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +1000
Subject: net: phy: realtek: fix RTL826x IRQ race and move firmware load to config_init

Three related timing problems cause IRQ lines for the RTL8261N/RTL8264B
to be permanently disabled ("nobody cared") on the Airoha AN7581 platform,
leaving phylib to fall back to polling (irq=POLL) on ~40-60% of boots:

1. EPROBE_DEFER loop: rtl8261n_probe() calls rtl826x_phy_patch_db_init()
   which uses request_firmware_direct() and returns -EPROBE_DEFER when
   rtl8261n.bin is not yet available (squashfs not mounted). The kernel
   retries probe at ~1s intervals. On AN7581, DSA (MT7530) initialises at
   ~T+11.76s and its internal IRQ mux immediately assigns live IRQ lines
   to the RTL8261N MDIO interrupt pins. A probe retry landing after that
   point resets the PHY (restoring VEND2:INER to its hardware default of
   0xf3f0, i.e. interrupts enabled) before any handler is registered.
   The resulting unhandled interrupt permanently disables the IRQ line for
   the session.

2. probe() to phy_attach_direct() window: even without the EPROBE_DEFER
   loop, VEND2:INER is enabled by default at probe time. Any autoneg or
   link event between probe() and phy_request_interrupt() fires with no
   handler registered.

3. Soft reset in config_init() restores VEND2:INER to 0xf3f0. A link-down
   event fires within milliseconds of reset deassert — well within the
   mandatory 30 ms settle period — before any INER mask write can occur.

Fix all three:

- Move firmware loading from probe() to config_init(): store the firmware
  filename in priv->fw_name at probe and call rtl826x_phy_patch_db_init()
  from rtl826x_config_init() when priv->patch is still NULL. By the time
  any network interface is brought up squashfs is guaranteed to be mounted,
  so the firmware is always available and -EPROBE_DEFER is never needed.
  Make rtl826x_phy_patch_db_init() non-static and export it for this use.

- Mask VEND2:INER to 0 in rtl826x_probe() (closes window 2).

- Mask VEND2:INER to 0 immediately after reset deassert in
  rtl826x_config_init(), before the 30 ms settle (closes window 3).
  rtl826x_config_intr() re-enables VEND2:INER once phy_request_interrupt()
  has registered the handler.

--- a/drivers/net/phy/realtek/realtek.h
